South Africa&#8217;s Chamber of Mines said it will raise a court challenge against a new mining charter announced earlier on Thursday by the mines minister that increased the minimum threshold for black ownership of mining firms to 30 percent from 26 percent. South Africa&#8217;s mining industry has said that it has not been consulted enough and it is losing investment as a result. READ MORE: Zwane raises mining sector black ownership requirement to 30% For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.